 • Cash on Hand (ending) = -1,980,427.60
 • Bank Deposits (ending) = 385,137.69
 • Total Cash = -1,980,427.60 + 385,137.69 = -1,595,289.91

Step 2: Identify the current debt, which is represented by Total Current Liabilities.
 • Total Current Liabilities = 1,015,922.54

Step 3: Calculate the Cash to Current Debt Ratio.
 • Cash to Current Debt Ratio = Total Cash / Total Current Liabilities = -1,595,289.91 / 1,015,922.54 ≈ -1.57
